  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "When اسم الفاعل Takes Objects",
      "titleArabic": "شروط إعمال اسم الفاعل",
      "content": [
        "اسم الفاعل can take a direct object like its verb, but this requires certain conditions.",
        "It must indicate present or future time and be preceded by negation, a question, or describe a noun."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Must indicate present/future (not past)",
        "Conditions: 1) Preceded by negation (ما ضاربٌ)",
        "2) Preceded by question particle (أَضَارِبٌ أَنْتَ؟)",
        "3) Used as a description (هذا رجلٌ ضاربٌ زيدًا)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مَا ضَارِبٌ زَيْدًا أَخُوكَ", "english": "Your brother is not hitting Zaid" },
        { "arabic": "أَقَارِئٌ الْكِتَابَ مُحَمَّدٌ؟", "english": "Is Muhammad reading the book?" },
        { "arabic": "هَذَا رَجُلٌ ضَارِبٌ ابْنَهُ", "english": "This is a man hitting his son" },
        { "arabic": "الطَّالِبُ حَافِظٌ دَرْسَهُ", "english": "The student is memorizing his lesson" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "اسم الفاعل with ال",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الفاعل المعرف بأل",
      "content": [
        "When اسم الفاعل has ال, it can take an object without the previous conditions.",
        "It acts more like a noun but retains its verbal force. Example: الضَّارِبُ زَيْدًا (the one hitting Zaid)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "With ال: acts freely as verb - الضَّارِبُ زَيْدًا",
        "Without ال: needs conditions (negation/question/description)",
        "Object always in accusative case",
        "Can also take prepositional complements"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الضَّارِبُ زَيْدًا", "english": "The one hitting Zaid came" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ الْقَارِئَ الْكِتَابَ", "english": "I saw the one reading the book" },
        { "arabic": "الْكَاتِبُ الرِّسَالَةَ حَاضِرٌ", "english": "The one writing the letter is present" },
        { "arabic": "هُوَ الْحَافِظُ الْقُرْآنَ", "english": "He is the one memorizing the Quran" }
      ]
    }
  ],
